description.undefined: Material ontology in the context of supply and value chain of the automotive industry. Exchange of material information and knowledge.

definition.value: An entity that exists in a physical form.
A product that is ready for sale.
A process is a set of activities that interact to produce a result; it has inputs and outputs, and a sequence of steps that in some way transform the inputs into the outputs.
A organization is a group of people who work together to achieve a common goal.
An action is an activity or movement that is done in order to achieve a goal.
A material that is used for production and does not become part of the product.
A material that is used in small amounts in the production of a product and becomes part of the product.
A place is a specific location.
An intermediate product is a product that is used as a raw material or ingredient in the production of other products.
Raw material that yielded from recycling of waste.
An event is something that happens at a given place and time.
A digital twin is a digital representation of an objects  from the real world. Are intended for data exchange.
A material that is used in the production of a product and becomes part of the product.
A product is a good or service that is offered for sale.
A person is a human being.
A specification is a document that outlines the requirements for a product, system, or service.
The AAS is the digital representation of an asset .
Things that are used for the production of a product.
An entity that exists in a non-physical form.
A Business Partner is a legal entity that is part of the Catena-X network or that stands in a relevant relation to a Catena-X Business Partner.
An Asset is any artifact that is provisioned/owned/attributed to some Catena-X Business Partner.
anything that has mass and takes up space
Raw material that are yielded from natural resources.
A unique identifier assigned incrementally or sequentially to an item, to uniquely identify it.
A string that identifies either a unique object or a unique class of objects.
The  Business Partner Number is a unique identifier following the pattern 'BPNL{8}{4}'.
The provisioned by predicate connects assets to their providing Catena-X Business Partner.
The  Business Partner Number Type describes strings following the pattern 'BPNL{8}{4}'.
The  Business Partner Number is a unique identifier following the pattern 'BPNL{8}{4}'.
The  Business Partner Number Type describes strings following the pattern 'BPNL{8}{4}'.
